23template <typename Container, typename Value>
24size_t RemoveFromMultimapByValue(Container* multimap, const Value& value) {
25 size_t count = 0;
26 for (auto it = multimap->begin(); it != multimap->end();) {
27 if (it->second == value) {
28 it = multimap->erase(it);
29 ++count;
30 } else {
31 ++it;
32 }
33 }
34 return count;
35}
36
37template <typename Map, typename Value>
38size_t RemoveFromMapByValue(Map* map, const Value& value) {
39 size_t count = 0;
40 for (auto it = map->begin(); it != map->end();) {
41 if (it->second == value) {
42 it = map->erase(it);
43 ++count;
44 } else {
45 ++it;
46 }
47 }
48 return count;
49}

53RtpDemuxerCriteria::RtpDemuxerCriteria() = default;
54RtpDemuxerCriteria::~RtpDemuxerCriteria() = default;
55
56bool RtpDemuxerCriteria::operator==(const RtpDemuxerCriteria& other) const {
57 return this->mid == other.mid && this->rsid == other.rsid &&
58 this->ssrcs == other.ssrcs &&
59 this->payload_types == other.payload_types;
60}
61
62bool RtpDemuxerCriteria::operator!=(const RtpDemuxerCriteria& other) const {
63 return !(*this == other);
64}
65
66std::string RtpDemuxerCriteria::ToString() const {
67 rtc::StringBuilder sb;
68 sb << "{mid: " << (mid.empty() ? "<empty>" : mid)
69 << ", rsid: " << (rsid.empty() ? "<empty>" : rsid) << ", ssrcs: [";
70
71 for (auto ssrc : ssrcs) {
72 sb << ssrc << ", ";
73 }
74
75 sb << "], payload_types = [";
76
77 for (auto pt : payload_types) {
78 sb << pt << ", ";
79 }
80
81 sb << "]}";
82 return sb.Release();
83}

85// static
86std::string RtpDemuxer::DescribePacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
87 rtc::StringBuilder sb;
88 sb << "PT=" << packet.PayloadType() << " SSRC=" << packet.Ssrc();
89 std::string mid;
90 if (packet.GetExtension<RtpMid>(&mid)) {
91 sb << " MID=" << mid;
92 }
93 std::string rsid;
94 if (packet.GetExtension<RtpStreamId>(&rsid)) {
95 sb << " RSID=" << rsid;
96 }
97 std::string rrsid;
98 if (packet.GetExtension<RepairedRtpStreamId>(&rrsid)) {
99 sb << " RRSID=" << rrsid;
100 }
101 return sb.Release();
102}

104RtpDemuxer::RtpDemuxer(bool use_mid /* = true*/) : use_mid_(use_mid) {}

106RtpDemuxer::~RtpDemuxer() {
107 RTC_DCHECK(sink_by_mid_.empty());
108 RTC_DCHECK(sink_by_ssrc_.empty());
109 RTC_DCHECK(sinks_by_pt_.empty());
110 RTC_DCHECK(sink_by_mid_and_rsid_.empty());
111 RTC_DCHECK(sink_by_rsid_.empty());
112}
113
114bool RtpDemuxer::AddSink(const RtpDemuxerCriteria& criteria,
115 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) {
116 RTC_DCHECK(!criteria.payload_types.empty() || !criteria.ssrcs.empty() ||
117 !criteria.mid.empty() || !criteria.rsid.empty());
118 RTC_DCHECK(criteria.mid.empty() || IsLegalMidName(criteria.mid));
119 RTC_DCHECK(criteria.rsid.empty() || IsLegalRsidName(criteria.rsid));
120 RTC_DCHECK(sink);
121
122 // We return false instead of DCHECKing for logical conflicts with the new
123 // criteria because new sinks are created according to user-specified SDP and
124 // we do not want to crash due to a data validation error.
125 if (CriteriaWouldConflict(criteria)) {
126 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Unable to add sink = " << sink
127 << " due conflicting criteria " << criteria.ToString();
128 return false;
129 }
130
131 if (!criteria.mid.empty()) {
132 if (criteria.rsid.empty()) {
133 sink_by_mid_.emplace(criteria.mid, sink);
134 } else {
135 sink_by_mid_and_rsid_.emplace(std::make_pair(criteria.mid, criteria.rsid),
136 sink);
137 }
138 } else {
139 if (!criteria.rsid.empty()) {
140 sink_by_rsid_.emplace(criteria.rsid, sink);
141 }
142 }
143
144 for (uint32_t ssrc : criteria.ssrcs) {
145 sink_by_ssrc_.emplace(ssrc, sink);
146 }
147
148 for (uint8_t payload_type : criteria.payload_types) {
149 sinks_by_pt_.emplace(payload_type, sink);
150 }
151
152 RefreshKnownMids();
153
154 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Added sink = " << sink << " for criteria "
155 << criteria.ToString();
156
157 return true;
158}
159
160bool RtpDemuxer::CriteriaWouldConflict(
161 const RtpDemuxerCriteria& criteria) const {
162 if (!criteria.mid.empty()) {
163 if (criteria.rsid.empty()) {
164 // If the MID is in the known_mids_ set, then there is already a sink
165 // added for this MID directly, or there is a sink already added with a
166 // MID, RSID pair for our MID and some RSID.
167 // Adding this criteria would cause one of these rules to be shadowed, so
168 // reject this new criteria.
169 if (known_mids_.find(criteria.mid) != known_mids_.end()) {
170 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << criteria.ToString()
171 << " would conflict with known mid";
172 return true;
173 }
174 } else {
175 // If the exact rule already exists, then reject this duplicate.
176 const auto sink_by_mid_and_rsid = sink_by_mid_and_rsid_.find(
177 std::make_pair(criteria.mid, criteria.rsid));
178 if (sink_by_mid_and_rsid != sink_by_mid_and_rsid_.end()) {
179 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << criteria.ToString()
180 << " would conflict with existing sink = "
181 << sink_by_mid_and_rsid->second
182 << " by mid+rsid binding";
183 return true;
184 }
185 // If there is already a sink registered for the bare MID, then this
186 // criteria will never receive any packets because they will just be
187 // directed to that MID sink, so reject this new criteria.
188 const auto sink_by_mid = sink_by_mid_.find(criteria.mid);
189 if (sink_by_mid != sink_by_mid_.end()) {
190 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << criteria.ToString()
191 << " would conflict with existing sink = "
192 << sink_by_mid->second << " by mid binding";
193 return true;
194 }
195 }
196 }
197
198 for (uint32_t ssrc : criteria.ssrcs) {
199 const auto sink_by_ssrc = sink_by_ssrc_.find(ssrc);
200 if (sink_by_ssrc != sink_by_ssrc_.end()) {
201 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << criteria.ToString()
202 << " would conflict with existing sink = "
203 << sink_by_ssrc->second << " binding by SSRC=" << ssrc;
204 return true;
205 }
206 }
207
208 // TODO(steveanton): May also sanity check payload types.
209
210 return false;
211}
212
213void RtpDemuxer::RefreshKnownMids() {
214 known_mids_.clear();
215
216 for (auto const& item : sink_by_mid_) {
217 const std::string& mid = item.first;
218 known_mids_.insert(mid);
219 }
220
221 for (auto const& item : sink_by_mid_and_rsid_) {
222 const std::string& mid = item.first.first;
223 known_mids_.insert(mid);
224 }
225}
226
227bool RtpDemuxer::AddSink(uint32_t ssrc, RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) {
228 RtpDemuxerCriteria criteria;
229 criteria.ssrcs.insert(ssrc);
230 return AddSink(criteria, sink);
231}
232
233void RtpDemuxer::AddSink(const std::string& rsid,
234 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) {
235 RtpDemuxerCriteria criteria;
236 criteria.rsid = rsid;
237 AddSink(criteria, sink);
238}
239
240bool RtpDemuxer::RemoveSink(const RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) {
241 RTC_DCHECK(sink);
242 size_t num_removed = RemoveFromMapByValue(&sink_by_mid_, sink) +
243 RemoveFromMapByValue(&sink_by_ssrc_, sink) +
244 RemoveFromMultimapByValue(&sinks_by_pt_, sink) +
245 RemoveFromMapByValue(&sink_by_mid_and_rsid_, sink) +
246 RemoveFromMapByValue(&sink_by_rsid_, sink);
247 RefreshKnownMids();
248 bool removed = num_removed > 0;
249 if (removed) {
250 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Removed sink = " << sink << " bindings";
251 }
252 return removed;
253}
254
255bool RtpDemuxer::OnRtpPacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
256 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink = ResolveSink(packet);
257 if (sink != nullptr) {
258 sink->OnRtpPacket(packet);
259 return true;
260 }
261 return false;
262}
263
264RtpPacketSinkInterface* RtpDemuxer::ResolveSink(
265 const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
266 // See the BUNDLE spec for high level reference to this algorithm:
267 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-mmusic-sdp-bundle-negotiation-38#section-10.2
268
269 // RSID and RRID are routed to the same sinks. If an RSID is specified on a
270 // repair packet, it should be ignored and the RRID should be used.
271 std::string packet_mid, packet_rsid;
272 bool has_mid = use_mid_ && packet.GetExtension<RtpMid>(&packet_mid);
273 bool has_rsid = packet.GetExtension<RepairedRtpStreamId>(&packet_rsid);
274 if (!has_rsid) {
275 has_rsid = packet.GetExtension<RtpStreamId>(&packet_rsid);
276 }
277 uint32_t ssrc = packet.Ssrc();
278
279 // The BUNDLE spec says to drop any packets with unknown MIDs, even if the
280 // SSRC is known/latched.
281 if (has_mid && known_mids_.find(packet_mid) == known_mids_.end()) {
282 return nullptr;
283 }
284
285 // Cache information we learn about SSRCs and IDs. We need to do this even if
286 // there isn't a rule/sink yet because we might add an MID/RSID rule after
287 // learning an MID/RSID<->SSRC association.
288
289 std::string* mid = nullptr;
290 if (has_mid) {
291 mid_by_ssrc_[ssrc] = packet_mid;
292 mid = &packet_mid;
293 } else {
294 // If the packet does not include a MID header extension, check if there is
295 // a latched MID for the SSRC.
296 const auto it = mid_by_ssrc_.find(ssrc);
297 if (it != mid_by_ssrc_.end()) {
298 mid = &it->second;
299 }
300 }
301
302 std::string* rsid = nullptr;
303 if (has_rsid) {
304 rsid_by_ssrc_[ssrc] = packet_rsid;
305 rsid = &packet_rsid;
306 } else {
307 // If the packet does not include an RRID/RSID header extension, check if
308 // there is a latched RSID for the SSRC.
309 const auto it = rsid_by_ssrc_.find(ssrc);
310 if (it != rsid_by_ssrc_.end()) {
311 rsid = &it->second;
312 }
313 }
314
315 // If MID and/or RSID is specified, prioritize that for demuxing the packet.
316 // The motivation behind the BUNDLE algorithm is that we trust these are used
317 // deliberately by senders and are more likely to be correct than SSRC/payload
318 // type which are included with every packet.
319 // TODO(steveanton): According to the BUNDLE spec, new SSRC mappings are only
320 // accepted if the packet's extended sequence number is
321 // greater than that of the last SSRC mapping update.
322 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7941#section-4.2.6
323 if (mid != nullptr) {
324 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink_by_mid = ResolveSinkByMid(*mid, ssrc);
325 if (sink_by_mid != nullptr) {
326 return sink_by_mid;
327 }
328
329 // RSID is scoped to a given MID if both are included.
330 if (rsid != nullptr) {
331 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink_by_mid_rsid =
332 ResolveSinkByMidRsid(*mid, *rsid, ssrc);
333 if (sink_by_mid_rsid != nullptr) {
334 return sink_by_mid_rsid;
335 }
336 }
337
338 // At this point, there is at least one sink added for this MID and an RSID
339 // but either the packet does not have an RSID or it is for a different
340 // RSID. This falls outside the BUNDLE spec so drop the packet.
341 return nullptr;
342 }
343
344 // RSID can be used without MID as long as they are unique.
345 if (rsid != nullptr) {
346 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink_by_rsid = ResolveSinkByRsid(*rsid, ssrc);
347 if (sink_by_rsid != nullptr) {
348 return sink_by_rsid;
349 }
350 }
351
352 // We trust signaled SSRC more than payload type which is likely to conflict
353 // between streams.
354 const auto ssrc_sink_it = sink_by_ssrc_.find(ssrc);
355 if (ssrc_sink_it != sink_by_ssrc_.end()) {
356 return ssrc_sink_it->second;
357 }
358
359 // Legacy senders will only signal payload type, support that as last resort.
360 return ResolveSinkByPayloadType(packet.PayloadType(), ssrc);
361}
362
363RtpPacketSinkInterface* RtpDemuxer::ResolveSinkByMid(const std::string& mid,
364 uint32_t ssrc) {
365 const auto it = sink_by_mid_.find(mid);
366 if (it != sink_by_mid_.end()) {
367 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink = it->second;
368 AddSsrcSinkBinding(ssrc, sink);
369 return sink;
370 }
371 return nullptr;
372}
373
374RtpPacketSinkInterface* RtpDemuxer::ResolveSinkByMidRsid(
375 const std::string& mid,
376 const std::string& rsid,
377 uint32_t ssrc) {
378 const auto it = sink_by_mid_and_rsid_.find(std::make_pair(mid, rsid));
379 if (it != sink_by_mid_and_rsid_.end()) {
380 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink = it->second;
381 AddSsrcSinkBinding(ssrc, sink);
382 return sink;
383 }
384 return nullptr;
385}
386
387RtpPacketSinkInterface* RtpDemuxer::ResolveSinkByRsid(const std::string& rsid,
388 uint32_t ssrc) {
389 const auto it = sink_by_rsid_.find(rsid);
390 if (it != sink_by_rsid_.end()) {
391 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink = it->second;
392 AddSsrcSinkBinding(ssrc, sink);
393 return sink;
394 }
395 return nullptr;
396}
397
398RtpPacketSinkInterface* RtpDemuxer::ResolveSinkByPayloadType(
399 uint8_t payload_type,
400 uint32_t ssrc) {
401 const auto range = sinks_by_pt_.equal_range(payload_type);
402 if (range.first != range.second) {
403 auto it = range.first;
404 const auto end = range.second;
405 if (std::next(it) == end) {
406 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink = it->second;
407 AddSsrcSinkBinding(ssrc, sink);
408 return sink;
409 }
410 }
411 return nullptr;
412}
413
414void RtpDemuxer::AddSsrcSinkBinding(uint32_t ssrc,
415 RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) {
416 if (sink_by_ssrc_.size() >= kMaxSsrcBindings) {
417 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "New SSRC=" << ssrc
418 << " sink binding ignored; limit of" << kMaxSsrcBindings
419 << " bindings has been reached.";
420 return;
421 }
422
423 auto result = sink_by_ssrc_.emplace(ssrc, sink);
424 auto it = result.first;
425 bool inserted = result.second;
426 if (inserted) {
427 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Added sink = " << sink
428 << " binding with SSRC=" << ssrc;
429 } else if (it->second != sink) {
430 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Updated sink = " << sink
431 << " binding with SSRC=" << ssrc;
432 it->second = sink;
433 }
434}
